<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALLAN MALAMUD: NOTES ON A SCORECARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALLAN MALAMUD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
There is something distressing about the grandson of them all, the Blockbuster 
Bowl, having a better attraction than the Rose Bowl. . . . 
</P>
<P>
I mean, would you rather watch Penn State, holder of the nation's longest 
winning streak, against Florida State, or Washington against Iowa, loser of two 
of its past three games? . . . 
</P>
<P>
Of course, the Rose Bowl has only itself to blame for the number of blah 
matchups in recent years. It got locked into this Pacific 10-Big Ten thing. 
Otherwise, such powers as Notre Dame, Miami and Penn State would have been 
taking the money and running in Pasadena on New Year's Day. . . . 
</P>
<P>
The last time two teams played for the national championship in Pasadena was 
after the 1968 season when Ohio State defeated USC, 27-16. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Teams with at least four defeats will be appearing in seven bowl games. . . . 
</P>
<P>
The resurgence of Minnesota is no blessing for the Raiders, who must play the 
Vikings on the road Dec. 22. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Marcus Allen is still the best running back in town. . . . 
</P>
<P>
This time it was a Plan B free-agent acquisition on the other side, Kansas City 
nose guard Dan Saleaumua, who helped decide a Raider game. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Don't tell anybody, but Joe Montana had a lousy game against the Rams. . . . 
What do Dan Marino, Boomer Esiason, Bubby Brister, Jim Kelly and Bernie Kosar 
have in common besides being AFC quarterbacks? All have had candy bars named 
after them. . . . 
</P>
<P>
This is a season the New England Patriots would like to forget, but their Ray 
Agnew may be the best rookie defensive lineman in the league. . . . 
</P>
<P>
The way the Falcons and Hawks are going, there must be a lot of talk about the 
1996 Olympic Games in Atlanta. . . . 
</P>
<P>
"Bo Knows Bo," heads the United Press International's nonfiction best-seller 
list. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Baltimore took the early lead in the George Bell sweepstakes, but now the 
Chicago Cubs are making a major bid for the Toronto free-agent outfielder. . . 
. 
</P>
<P>
General Manager Al Rosen of the San Francisco Giants, who has been criticized 
for giving Bud Black $10 million, says major league teams are spending so much 
money on pitchers because there aren't many good ones in the minor leagues. . . 
. 
</P>
<P>
Official paid attendance for the Evander Holyfield-Buster Douglas fight at the 
Mirage Oct. 25 in Las Vegas was 9,637 in a 16,000-seat stadium and the gate a 
disappointing $6,129,500. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Terry Norris, the World Boxing Council junior middleweight champion who will 
defend his title Feb. 9 against Sugar Ray Leonard at Madison Square Garden, 
will box an eight-round exhibition at the Country Club in Reseda tonight. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Exotic locale for International Boxing Federation junior flyweight champion 
Michael Carbajal's Dec. 8 shootout with Leon Salazar will be the Rawhide 
Western Theme Park in Scottsdale, Ariz. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Happy 92nd birthday to Tom Gallery, the former boxing promoter and head of NBC 
Sports who is convalescing at Tarzana Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
If they can, the Clippers should trade Gary Grant to Indiana for the steady 
Vern Fleming. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Bo Kimble will make an ideal sixth man when Ron Harper returns to the Clipper 
lineup. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Kareem Abdul-Jabbar joined Magic Johnson on the sidelines at the Raider-Kansas 
City game. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Depth is among the reasons for the success of the Portland Trail Blazers, who 
go 10 deep. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Al Bianchi, the New York Knicks' general manager, should bring back Bernard 
King, who is being made available by the Washington Bullets. . . . 
</P>
<P>
Cazzie Russell, who was an assistant to Mike Fratello in Atlanta, has been 
named coach of the Grand Rapids Hoops of the Continental Basketball Assn. . . . 
New Loyola Marymount Coach Jay Hillock must have learned defense from Paul 
Westhead. . . . 
</P>
<P>
If Arizona keeps playing the way it did against Arkansas, I may have to retract 
that statement about the Nevada Las Vegas-less NCAA tournament determining 
which team is second best in the nation. . . . 
</P>
<P>
