<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: EVEREST &amp; JENNINGS LOSES $38 MILLION IN 3RD QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Everest &amp; Jennings International Ltd., citing restructuring costs, said it 
lost $38.4 million in the third quarter, compared with a $2.84-million loss a 
year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
The latest loss was expected. 
</P>
<P>
The Camarillo-based maker of wheelchairs and other medical equipment had last 
week predicted that it would post a "substantial" loss because it would take a 
charge to cover the restructuring costs and the writedown in the value of 
certain assets. The charge totaled $32.4 million for the quarter that ended 
Sept. 30. 
</P>
<P>
Everest &amp; Jenning's revenue in the quarter rose to $53.5 million from $48.7 
million. 
</P>
<P>
For the first nine months of this year, the company lost $46.5 million on 
revenue of $156.3 million. In the comparable 1989 period, it lost $9.46 million 
on revenue of $138 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
