<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CLAUDIA PUIG , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Time Is on Their Side: Mick Jagger and his longtime girlfriend, Texas model 
Jerry Hall, were married on the Indonesian island of Bali, the Rolling Stones 
press agent said Monday. The wedding took place Wednesday and few details were 
available, except that it was a traditional Indonesian ceremony, and the 
couple's two children, Elizabeth, 6, and James, 5, attended, a spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
"Even we didn't hear about it until today, so they have clearly managed to keep 
the wedding very secret," said the spokesman. The couple have been together for 
more than 10 years. British-born Jagger was divorced from first wife, Bianca, 
in 1979. Hall has not been married before. Alan Dunn, Jagger's longstanding 
friend and the Rolling Stones' tour director, was the best man. CLAUDIA PUIG 
</P>
