<TEXT>
<P>
More Vanilli: To guard against future Milli Vanilli-like scams, two Boston-area 
lawmakers filed a bill Monday to prevent singing groups from giving audiences 
nothing but lip service in Massachusetts. "If you pay 'real' money for a 
concert, you ought to get 'real' live music in return," said Rep. Kevin 
Poirier. The bill would require promoters to disclose whether any part of a 
performance consists of recorded vocals. CLAUDIA PUIG 
