<TEXT>
<P>
'Cafe' Closes: "Bagdad Cafe," the CBS comedy starring Whoopi Goldberg and Jean 
Stapleton, has gone out of production, CBS confirmed Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Sources close to the show say production shut down after a dispute between 
Goldberg and the show's co-executive producer, Thad Mumford, during a Nov. 16 
taping. A CBS spokeswoman said the network had not yet determined a date the 
show would go off the air. Goldberg's representatives had no immediate comment 
on the matter. CLAUDIA PUIG 
