decision on its future is expected by Dec. 15. NBC also disclosed that two of 
its new sitcoms -- "Working It Out" and "The Fanelli Boys" -- will switch time 
slots beginning Wednesday. "Working It Out," will move to 9:30 p.m. Wednesday, 
and "The Fanelli Boys" to 8:30 p.m. Saturday. The low-rated medical anthology 
"Lifestories" will be seen on a monthly basis for the remainder of the season, 
