<HEADLINE>
<P>
DR. WILLARD B. CROSLEY; RETIRED PHYSICIAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dr. Willard B. Crosley, a retired obstetrician-gynecologist and former chief of 
staff of Glendale Memorial Hospital and Health Center, has died at his Glendale 
home. He was 79. 
</P>
<P>
Crosley died Nov. 20 of complications from a fall in July, said his wife, Dr. 
Donna C. Crosley. 
</P>
<P>
He was born July 1, 1911, in Chicago and received his medical degree from 
Western Reserve University in Cleveland in 1940. 
</P>
<P>
Six years later, he opened his practice in Burbank and joined the staff of 
Glendale Memorial Hospital and Health Center. 
</P>
<P>
In 1949, Crosley relocated to Glendale, where he practiced with the group of 
Wilkinson, Crosley &amp; McNicholas. He served as the hospital's chief in 1966 
and as chairman of its board of directors in 1980-81. He retired in 1984 after 
delivering more than 5,000 babies, according to his wife. 
</P>
<P>
Crosley was a member of the Los Angeles County Medical Assn. and the Los 
Angeles County Obstetrical and Gynecological Society. 
</P>
<P>
He is survived by his wife of 45 years, Dr. Donna C. Crosley, a pediatrician; 
son Jon Crosley of South Pasadena; daughter Madeline Rasmuson of Sebastopol, 
Calif.; four brothers and two grandchildren. 
</P>
<P>
A graveside service is scheduled today at 11 a.m. at Grand View Memorial Park, 
1341 Glenwood Road, Glendale. Eckerman-Heisman Funeral Service in Burbank is 
handling the arrangements. 
</P>
<P>
Donations can be made in Crosley's name to the Nursing Education Fund at 
Glendale Memorial Hospital and Health Center or to Grandview Presbyterian 
Church in Glendale. 
</P>
</TEXT>
