<HEADLINE>
<P>
DRIVER ARRESTED AFTER 3 ACCIDENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A suspected drunk driver caused at least three traffic accidents Monday, 
including one that broke a water main, flooding Sherman Way in Van Nuys for an 
hour and a half, Los Angeles police said. 
</P>
<P>
Ramon Antonio Sandoval, 32, of Van Nuys was arrested on suspicion of felony 
drunk driving, Officer Walter Hogue said. 
</P>
<P>
Police said Sandoval struck one vehicle that was stopped at a curb at Sherman 
Way and Sepulveda Boulevard while the occupants read a map. "He fled from that 
accident with them chasing him," Hogue said. "He jumped a center divider, hit a 
westbound car and that car hit another car." 
</P>
<P>
Sandoval's car struck a water main on the center divider, sending water 
shooting into the air, police said. Westbound lanes of Sherman Way were closed 
for an hour and a half while workers repaired the broken line. 
</P>
