<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: PUBLIC INPUT SOUGHT ON NEW AREA CODES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Orange County residents will have a chance to evaluate and comment on proposals 
to split the 714 area code during two meetings sponsored by GTE and Pacific 
Bell this week. 
</P>
<P>
Both companies recommend a plan that would keep all of Orange County in the 714 
area. 
</P>
<P>
Riverside and San Bernardino counties, as well as Claremont, Diamond Bar and 
Pomona in eastern Los Angeles County, would be placed in a new 909 area, phone 
company officials said. The new boundaries will be announced in January, after 
evaluation of customer input, and take effect about two years later. 
</P>
<P>
The first meeting will be held from 7 to 9 tonight at the Brea Civic and 
Cultural Center at 1 Civic Center Circle. 
</P>
<P>
Another meeting will take place on Friday at Irvine City Hall, 1 Civic Center 
Plaza, from 7 to 9 p.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
