<HEADLINE>
<P>
CANYON, VILLA PARK PLAYERS SIGN WITH USC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANAHEIM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Greg Tippin of Canyon High School and Aaron Boone of Villa Park have signed 
letters of intent to play baseball at USC, Boone and Canyon Coach Hi Lavalle 
said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Tippin, the Comanches' co-captain, plays first base, outfield and also pitches. 
</P>
<P>
He hit .355 last season with three home runs and 18 runs batted in. As a 
pitcher, he had a record of 3-4 with a 2.54 earned-run average. 
</P>
<P>
Boone hit .370 and had 13 stolen bases for Villa Park last season and will play 
infield for USC. 
</P>
</TEXT>
