</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chevron to Stop Selling Solvents: Citing the growing cost of environmental 
regulations, the San Francisco firm said it would stop making thinners and 
solvents by Jan. 31. 
</P>
<P>
Chevron is the largest West Coast manufacturer of thinners, used in paints, dry 
cleaning, charcoal lighter fluid, concrete curing, food processing and 
industrial cleaners. The company makes thinners and solvents at its El Segundo 
and Salt Lake City refineries. Discontinuing the products, which are byproducts 
of gasoline and jet fuel manufacturing, will reduce operating costs at the 
refineries but not result in the loss of any jobs, Chevron said. 
</P>
