<TEXT>
<P>
Microwave Corp., AT&amp;T Form Venture: The two companies said they have 
entered into an agreement to develop advanced microwave radio products for use 
in phone networks and private radio systems. 
</P>
<P>
The two will develop digital radio products that will use a new industry 
standard to send signals over the air through the fiber-optic cables 
increasingly used in telephone networks. The new standard is based on a 
technology called synchronous digital hierarchy transmission. Both companies 
will market the new radio products, with American Telephone &amp; Telegraph Co. 
concentrating on high-capacity applications and Digital Microwave on low- to 
medium-capacity uses. 
</P>
