<P>
More Oil Rigs in Service: After two weeks of declines, the number of rigs 
searching for oil and gas in the United States climbed by 72 this week to 1,175 
nationwide, Baker Hughes Inc. reported. At the height of the oil boom in 
December, 1981, the count reached a record 4,500. It plunged to a low of 663 
after oil prices collapsed in the summer of 1986. 
