THE WEEK AHEAD: UNITED NATIONS; 
</P>
<P>
DEBATING 'NECESSARY MEANS' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The United Nations Security Council, with foreign ministers holding down most 
of the 15 chairs in order to give the debate added authority, weighs a 
U.S.-backed resolution Thursday authorizing the use of military force to get 
Iraq out of Kuwait if peaceful measures continue to founder. 
</P>
<P>
Advance drafts of the resolution omit the word "force" in favor of "all 
necessary means," but the meaning is clear. 
</P>
<P>
The council warms up for the vote with a two-day debate today and Wednesday 
about Iraqi atrocities in Kuwait. The exiled Kuwaiti government plans to kick 
off that session. 
</P>
