<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD; 
</P>
<P>
NO EVIDENCE OF IRAQ A-WEAPONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
VIENNA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Outside inspectors have found no evidence that Iraq is diverting nuclear 
material from its civilian research program for military use, the International 
Atomic Energy Agency said today. In a brief statement on a visit to Iraq by 
inspectors last week, the IAEA said no change had taken place in the status of 
nuclear material under agency safeguards since a previous inspection in April. 
</P>
</TEXT>
