<P>
P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
EC DELAYS PROCTER-FINAF VENTURE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BRUSSELS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The European Community Commission asked Procter &amp; Gamble Co. of the United 
States and Italy's Finaf SpA today to suspend a plan to cooperate on making 
diapers and other personal hygienic products. 
</P>
<P>
The companies said in September they planned to create joint ventures in Italy, 
Spain and Portugal for their paper products businesses, notably diapers and 
sanitary napkins. 
</P>
<P>
Procter said it would buy all Finaf's activities in Britain. 
</P>
<P>
The commission asked the companies to hold off until it is satisfied "there is 
no breach" of EC fair competition rules. 
</P>
<P>
A commission official said the accord could create or strengthen dominant 
positions by the two companies and said it had received a complaint about the 
planned venture from Peau Douce SA, a French diaper maker. 
</P>
</TEXT>
